Danny (our accountant/bean counter) has been hitting the gym recently, so he loves to sneak in a bit of extra protein into his diet wherever he can. Recently he's been spicing things up in the kitchen by mixing high protein pseudo-cereal quinoa with all the freshness of grated courgette and the vibrant colour of turmeric. The end result is a little plate of freshness to brighten up the winter!

== Courgette Quinoa Patties ==

Boil a #large pot{} of water for your @quinoa{1/2%cup}. Grate half of @courgette{1.5}(grated) on the large-holed side of a #grater{}. Squeeze out all the water and press between #kitchen towel{} if you have some. Chop the other half of the courgette, the @coriander{1/3%bunch}(chopped), the @mint leaves{2}(chopped) and finely slice a @garlic clove{1}.

Rinse the quinoa under running water for ~{1%minute} then add to the boiling water. Gently simmer the quinoa with 1/2 the @vegetable stock pot{1/2} for around ~{15%minutes}. Test the quinoa for 'done-ness' and drain it once it's soft enough to eat.

> Tip: Prepare in advance and let it cool down completely for best results.

Heat 2 tsp of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #pan{} and cook the garlic for ~{1%minute}. Add all the courgettes with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} and cook for ~{3%mins}. Add the quinoa and @turmeric{1/2%tsp} and thoroughly mix. Remove from the heat.

Mix in the @plain flour{3%tbsp}, the fresh coriander, @grated hard Italian style cheese{2%tbsp} and 1-2 tbsp @Greek style yoghurt{1-2%tbsp}. Let the mixture cool down for about ~{10%mins}.

> Tip: Add more or less yoghurt to make sure the patties are not too moist.
> Tip: To cool it down quickly, lay it all out flat on a baking tray and put it in the fridge.

Form the mixture into 4 equal sized patties.

> Tip: Make sure they are compact so they don't fall apart later.

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium heat with 1 tbsp of @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Very gently place the patties in the oil and cook for ~{3-4%mins} on each side until golden.

== Minted Yoghurt Sauce ==

Whisk the remaining @Greek style yoghurt{1%tbsp} with the finely chopped fresh @mint leaves{remaining}(finely chopped).

Chop the @cherry tomatoes{1}(chopped in half) and mix with the @salad leaves{2%handfuls}. Dress with a little @olive oil{little} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Serve the patties on the salad with the minted yoghurt sauce on top.